  <fieldset>

    <h2>Automated Archiving/Backup</h2>
    <a href="/images/backup_sample.jpg" class="lightview"><img src="/images/backup_sample.jpg" width="252" height="181" alt="Automated / Continuous Import" class="floatleft" /></a>
    <p>
      Once you choose what services you'd like to backup (Facebook, Twitter, etc.), Eternos automatically and continuously archives your data. The services we support include Facebook, Twitter, Picasa, Gmail, Tumblr, Wordpress, any blog or RSS feed, with many more to come! Automated archiving is the very core of our service, it is the easiest means of chronicling your life. 
    </p>

    <hr  />
    
    <h2>Your Timeline</h2>
    <a href="/images/timeline_large.jpg" class="lightview"><img src="/images/timeline_large.jpg" width="252" height="181" alt="Timeline" class="floatleft" /></a>
    <p>
      Once you're personal artifacts* are imported into your Eternos account, they are set to a timeline that you can scroll through by age, day, month or year. View specific items at any point of your timeline by placing your cursor over the corresponding icon on your timeline. For example, if you post a status update, that will appear as a Facebook icon on your timeline. When you place your cursor on that icon, you'll see a popup box that displays the event or artifact. (for example, an old family photo).
      <br/><br/>
      * Artifacts = Your archived activity, emails, photos, videos, and files.
    </p>

    <hr  />    
    
    <h2>Easy Event Editing</h2>
    <a href="/images/artifactediting_large.jpg" class="lightview"><img src="/images/artifactediting_large.jpg" width="252" height="181" alt="Easy Event / Artifact Editing" class="floatleft" /></a>
    <p>
      Use this feature to tag events for easy reference, delete artifacts you don't want in your archive, and to assign viewing permissions for posterity.
    </p>

    <hr  />
    
    <h2>Search and Tag Cloud</h2>
    <a href="/images/search_large.jpg" class="lightview"><img src="/images/search_large.jpg" width="252" height="181" alt="Search" class="floatleft" /></a>
    <p>
      Events and Artifacts are automatically indexed into your personal search. Your tag cloud is a weighted list that shows what words and phrases appear most in your archive; clicking on the word or phrase performs a search for that keyword. These two features, along with the timeline, are essential tools for accessing and enjoying your artifacts.
    </p> 
    <hr  />
    
    <h2>Biographical Profile</h2>
    <a href="/images/profile_sample.png" class="lightview"><img src="/images/profile_sample.png" width="252" height="181" alt="Profile" class="floatleft" /></a>
    <p>
      Your eternos archive has a full featured biographical survey for you to fill out (if you like). The information you enter will be shared with future generations. Not only will your Eternos profile give your descendants valuable insight into your life, it will provide them with medical data that might be important for them to know. For example, a history of heart disease or diabetes.
    </p>
    <hr/>
    
  <h2>Life Key</h2>
  <a href="/images/lifekey_large.jpg" class="lightview"><img src="/images/lifekey_large.jpg" width="252" height="181" alt="Life Key" class="floatleft" /></a>
  <p>
    Life Key is the tool you'll utilize if you want to pass your archive on to loved ones in the event of your passing. Once we have confirm that you have passed on, we will provide your loved ones with access to your archive based upon your wishes. Life Key permissions can be revoked at any time during your lifetime. Only artifacts you choose to share will be viewable by your descendants. Life Key is the feature that ensures your legacy survives for generations to come and is highly recommended for members interested in Genealogy.
  </p>
